[/font]
[font=Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif]Excessively plump figures have become
increasingly prevalent in China, with around 25% of the country’s adult
population qualifying as either overweight or obese, according to the
University of North Carolina study. Two-thirds of U.S. adults are overweight or
obese.[/font]
