Date:7/26/2011 1:34:44 AM
From:Spekulatius
I think you are correct, this debt limit drama is one of those cases, where
there is very little upside but a lot of downside. Even if a deal is made, I
see a situation where roughly 10% of the GNP (15 Trillion us$) is generated by
the deficit (1.5$ trillion Us$). So, if we go into a self sustaining situation
where the deficit stays the same, the GNP would be 10% lower.
Of course, that would never work that way because -10% GNP would be a disaster,
but that just shows the severity of the situation. Any cut in spending, will
cause a corresponding reduction in GNP - since the numbers are so large, there
are going to be severe headwinds in growth for many years and maybe decades. I
see little good coming out of this for the stock market, no matter what the
solution.
