%BOM---------------------
Date:7/26/2011 8:42:37 PM
From:Spekulatius
Of course congressman are not complete idiots, but history shows that a group
of smart people, acting by virtue of competing parties can come up with very
boneheaded results. Then, there is also the risk that they wait until the last
minute to resolve the differences, a technicality prevents them from raising
the limit, even if they intend to do so. Last not least there is a case to be
made that, regardless of circumstances; if a country is only a couple of days
away from default, it can't be considered AAA any more. This is because in the
end, paying or not for a sovereign is a matter of political will to use the
governmental powers to pay their debtors.
If that cannot be considered a given any more, foreign debtors should not
consider sovereign debt safe. Sovereign debt is not like debt of a company
where in case of a default, the debtors have the claim to the assets. The
sovereign owners are the people and the government body and if they don't pay,
the debtors are basically out of luck - they cannot claim anything in most
cases.
